plt.dataset

Interface DataSet

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DumpDataSet, ExperimentDataset, ObjectsOrderFormat

    public interface DataSet
    A DataSet is composed by a set of objects, a set of functions for the objects called features, and a set of pairwise preference called instances. A dataSet can't be used as input for the preference learning algorithms: a TrainableDataSet must be constructed and then used.
    Author:
    Vincent Farrugia
